  "headline": "F041a_SURVIVES_CONDUCTOR_CONTROL",
  "reading": "Joint regression b_nbp = 0.4706 (z=3.37) >= 3.0 after controlling for mean log-conductor and interaction. Interaction term z = 2.9828909295980486. Narrow-bin corr(nbp, slope) = 0.964691769509398. The nbp effect on first-moment conductor-slope is not merely the shadow of within-decade conductor drift; arithmetic structure survives.",
